{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id5fde0649-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58","identifier":"/us/usc/t30/s49b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"49b"},"text":"§ 49b.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Mining laws relating to placer claims extended to Alaska","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The general mining laws of the United States so far as they are applicable to placer-mining claims, as prior to ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1934-05-04"},"text":"May 4, 1934","children":[],"tail":", extended to the Territory of Alaska, are declared to be in full force and effect in said Territory: "},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"Provided","children":[],"tail":", That nothing herein shall be held to change or affect the rights acquired by locators or owners of placer-mining claims prior to "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1934-05-04"},"text":"May 4, 1934","children":[],"tail":", located in said Territory under act "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1912-08-01"},"text":"August 1, 1912","children":[],"tail":" ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/37/242"},"text":"37 Stat. 242","children":[],"tail":", 243) and amendatory act "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1925-03-03"},"text":"March 3, 1925","children":[],"tail":" ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/43/1118"},"text":"43 Stat. 1118","children":[],"tail":")."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id5fde064a-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1934-05-04/ch211/s2"},"text":"May 4, 1934, ch. 211, § 2","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/48/663"},"text":"48 Stat. 663","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id5fde064b-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id5fde064c-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id5fde064d-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1912-08-01"},"text":"August 1, 1912","children":[],"tail":" ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/37/242"},"text":"37 Stat. 242","children":[],"tail":", 243) and amenda­tory act "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1925-03-03"},"text":"March 3, 1925","children":[],"tail":" ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/43/1118"},"text":"43 Stat. 1118","children":[],"tail":"), referred to in text, were repealed by section 1 of act "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1934-05-04"},"text":"May 4, 1934","children":[],"tail":". See sections 35 to 37 and 49b of this title."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"id5fe0764e-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was formerly classified to sections 119 and 381a of Title 48, Territories and Insular Possessions.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id5fe0764f-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDate","id":"id5fe07650-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1934-05-04/ch211/s3"},"text":"Act May 4, 1934, ch. 211, § 3","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/48/663"},"text":"48 Stat. 663","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/act/1934-05-04/ch211/s3"},"text":"“This Act [enacting this section] shall take effect thirty days subsequent to the date of convening of the first regular session of the Alaska Territorial Legislature which is held after the passage of this Act [","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1934-05-04"},"text":"May 4, 1934","children":[],"tail":"].”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"execDoc","id":"id5fe07651-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Executive Documents","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"id5fe07652-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Admission of Alaska as State","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Admission of Alaska into the Union was accomplished ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1959-01-03"},"text":"Jan. 3, 1959","children":[],"tail":", on issuance of Proc. No. 3269, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1959-01-03"},"text":"Jan. 3, 1959","children":[],"tail":", 24 F.R. 81, 73 Stat. c16, as required by sections 1 and 8(c) of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/85/508"},"text":"Pub. L. 85–508","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1958-07-07"},"text":"July 7, 1958","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/72/339"},"text":"72 Stat. 339","children":[],"tail":", set out as notes preceding "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"h